Feature Plan: MoviesVC monochrome redesign with favorites and mocked ratings (UIKit)

Objective
- Redesign `MoviesVC` using `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/movies-redesign2.prototype.html` as primary design target (derived from `image0.png`).
- Add favorite toggles per movie.
- Display ratings from static JSON fixture (mock external API).
- Ensure footer navigation is not present in MoviesVC.
- Keep the existing MoviesVC search bar behavior.
- Remove segmented control and replace it with design-aligned category chips.
- Load available categories from existing backend movie payload when present, otherwise use iOS static fallback chips.

Constraints
- UIKit-only implementation.
- No backend API contract changes.
- Ratings source is local static fixture (Option A), not remote call.
- Category chips must not require backend API changes.

Role ownership
- Primary iOS implementation: `@ios-dev`
- Data contract and fallback behavior review: `@ios-dev`
- Regression validation: `@testing-engineer`

Target files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/MoviesVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Networking/` (only if light helper needed)
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/Resources/ratings-mock.json` (or existing resource bucket)
- `.specify/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/movies-redesign2.prototype.html`

High-level architecture
1. Visual layer
   - Refactor MoviesVC layout to match `movies-redesign2.prototype.html` hierarchy in monochrome style.
   - Remove/hide footer navigation region for MoviesVC.
   - Keep existing search bar visible and usable.
   - Remove segmented control and render horizontal category chips instead.
2. Categories baseline + iOS fallback
   - Read category values from existing movie payload fields when available.
   - Build deduplicated chip list in design order.
   - If categories are missing/empty, render iOS static fallback chips while keeping movie list usable.
3. Favorites
   - Add local favorite state keyed by movie identifier.
   - Render selected/unselected favorite icon state in list/grid cells.
4. Ratings mock fixture
   - Load static JSON fixture at screen init (or lazy load on first render).
   - Map fixture entries by `movieId` to view model.
   - Fallback to `N/A` when missing.
5. Error/fallback
   - If categories are unavailable from backend payload, keep movies render path active and show static fallback chips.
   - If fixture fails parsing, keep movie rendering and show fallback ratings.
6. Diagnostics
   - Log category source (`backend` or `fallback`) and mapped category count.
   - Log fixture load status and mapped rating count.

Mock fixture contract (Option A)
- Filename example: `ratings-mock.json`
- Suggested shape:
  - root: `ratings`
  - items: `{ "movieId": <Int>, "rating": <String> }`

Interaction behavior
- Favorite toggle is immediate and local.
- Rating display is read-only in this phase.
- No footer navigation controls in MoviesVC.
- Existing search bar remains the primary text search control.
- Segmented control is removed.
- Category chips are data-driven from existing backend payload values, with iOS static fallback.

Verification strategy
- Manual verify monochrome styling and `movies-redesign2.prototype.html` structure.
- Manual verify search bar is present and usable.
- Manual verify segmented control is absent.
- Manual verify category chips render from backend payload when available and degrade to static fallback values when missing.
- Manual verify favorite toggle visual states.
- Manual verify ratings show from fixture and fallback for missing entries.
- Manual verify no footer navigation in MoviesVC.
- Confirm UIKit-only implementation.

Definition of done
- MoviesVC follows `movies-redesign2.prototype.html` monochrome layout.
- Existing search bar remains available.
- Segmented control is removed.
- Category chips are supplied by backend payload when available, else static fallback values.
- Favorites and mocked ratings are visible and stable.
- Footer navigation is removed from MoviesVC.
- Static fixture load + fallback behavior confirmed.
- Category source detection (`backend` vs `fallback`) and fallback behavior confirmed.
- Prototype and speckit artifacts are complete and aligned.

